  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Institutionnal support 2017</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project has been designed to address needs in shelter and livelihoods, and capacity-building of local communities and authorities, with a strong focus on DRR principles, ensuring a holistic response that increases the resilience of affected communities to future shocks. On the other hand, KORAL will work to define new strategies of working although the designing of a new strategic plan enabling to lead to an organization more sustainable.  The community groups will be strengthened to be better organized to work with the local authorities and the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is to keep strengthening the capacity of the people affected by the hurricane Matthew and set up network of organizations in the South. This project is design to support KORAL to implement different activities with different donors as response to the hurricane Matthew and allow KORAL to build a new strategic plan for the next 3 years.</narrative>
  </description>
